Cook ground beef and onion in a large skillet until beef is crumbled and no longer pink; drain. Stir in tomatoes and season to taste; heat through. Coat a 13x9x2-inch baking dish with PAM No Stick Cooking Spray. Combine cooked pasta with meat-tomato mixture and mozzarella cheese. Pour into baking dish; top with Parmesan cheese. Bake in a preheated 350 degrees F oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until heated through and cheese is melted.